This paper discusses the use of virtual machine migration for resource management in cloud data centers, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of migration for load balancing and fault management, which are topics related to Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also briefly mentions the use of migration for real-time server maintenance, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a queue-based migration model, which is related to Programming Languages (cs.PL).
